cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper proposes an end-to-end learning scheme to address the bias in citizen science data. The paper focuses on the application of bird observational data from the citizen science project eBird. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper deals with learning schemes and data analysis. Additionally, the paper discusses the handling of massive high-dimensional data, which suggests the possibility of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as potential categories.
